title: JavaScript Execution via cscript.exe launched from cmd.exe (T1059.007)
id: b8e7a4f1-1059-007-cscript-cmd
status: experimental
author: Busra Ugur
date: 2026-01-31
description: |
  Detects JavaScript execution via Windows Script Host (cscript.exe)
  where the script is launched from cmd.exe, a common execution
  pattern observed in scripted attack chains and Atomic Red Team tests.

references:
  - https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1059/007/

logsource:
  product: windows
  category: process_creation

detection:
  selection_child:
    Image|endswith: '\cscript.exe'
    CommandLine|contains: '.js'

  selection_parent:
    ParentImage|endswith: '\cmd.exe'

  condition: selection_child and selection_parent

falsepositives:
  - Administrative batch scripts invoking JavaScript
  - Software installers using Windows Script Host

level: medium

tags:
  - attack.execution
  - attack.t1059.007
  - attack.lolbin
